01/05/2006
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska police announced the arrest Friday (28 April) of a Bosnian Serb suspected of war crimes in Ljubija, in the northern BiH municipality of Prijedor. Boro Milojica, 40, was detained in his home village of Tisovina. He is charged with crimes against local Muslims in 1992. 
In other news Friday, the BiH Court ordered a month's detention for other two Bosnian Serb suspects -- brothers Goran and Zoran Damjanovic -- who were arrested in eastern Sarajevo last week. They are charged with crimes against Bosniaks in the Sarajevo area during the war. (Fena, RTRS - 28/04/06)
